channel.name: Swe and Finance Internship - Please don't be nice to me.

messages.content: I am going into my sophomore year and would lilke to get an early start. Please don't be nice to me. Any pointers would be helpful. Thank you!!!!

- You dont have to say anticipated graduation date, just put May 2028
- The spacing between the subsection and the bar is kinda off
- Fix order of work experience - newest to oldest
- Try to adhere more to google xyz format for descriptions

I feel like the top isn’t centered 
XYZ format above for more meaningful bullet points 
Idt you need GitHub 
More bullet points could be good to get rid of white space
Ok thank you guys for the feedback!
Y no github? Also which part of the top do u not think is centered?
I meant as a skill sorry
I feel like it’s too far left
Oh yeah I kinda see it now weird
I feel like that generally frowned upon in a professional context?

as long as the personal email isnt something stupid like poopeater37@hotmail.com, it doesn't really matter whether you use a school or personal email. I use a personal one that is just for job apps and important things tho so I don't miss emails, whenever i used my school email things got more easily lost between all the other emails and garbage
You should abbreviate the month names, so Sept. instead of September. Nawk Nawk also has a typo in Researched, and the date says “June Present”. Ryan’s advice is good. Otherwise looks good.
Why do you say about the abbreviation
It increases readability, makes it more concise and overall look better
Same reason why LinkedIn doesn’t need to have the www, or even the .com honestly. A recruiter will understand in/name-here is a linked in url.
Rlly good resume going into sophomore year +1 what was said above
